The best approach for your .NET 10 project is **`System.IO.Abstractions`** — a battle-tested NuGet package that wraps the entire `System.IO` surface behind mockable interfaces. No need to write custom wrappers.

Here's how to adopt it for your `ReportGenerator`:

### 1. Install the packages

```bash
dotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions
dotnet add <YourTestProject> package System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers
```

### 2. Inject `IFileSystem` instead of using statics

```csharp
using System.IO.Abstractions;

namespace NeedsWrappers.Services;

public class ReportGenerator(IFileSystem fileSystem)
{
    public string GenerateReport(string reportName)
    {
        var timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("yyyyMMdd_HHmmss");
        var outputDir = Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("REPORT_OUTPUT_DIR") ?? "/tmp/reports";

        if (!fileSystem.Directory.Exists(outputDir))
        {
            fileSystem.Directory.CreateDirectory(outputDir);
        }

        var reportPath = fileSystem.Path.Combine(outputDir, $"{reportName}_{timestamp}.txt");
        var content = $"Report: {reportName}\nGenerated: {DateTime.UtcNow:O}\nMachine: {Environment.MachineName}";

        fileSystem.File.WriteAllText(reportPath, content);
        Console.WriteLine($"Report written to {reportPath}");

        return reportPath;
    }
}
```

### 3. Register in DI

```csharp
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IFileSystem, FileSystem>();
```

### 4. Test with `MockFileSystem`

```csharp
using System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers;

var mockFs = new MockFileSystem();
// MockFileSystem starts with no directories — they're created on the fly
var generator = new ReportGenerator(mockFs);

var path = generator.GenerateReport("sales");

// Assert the file was written
Assert.True(mockFs.File.Exists(path));
var content = mockFs.File.ReadAllText(path);
Assert.Contains("Report: sales", content);
```

### Bonus: your other statics

Your `ReportGenerator` also uses `DateTime.UtcNow` and `Environment.*`. These have their own recommended abstractions:

| Static | Recommendation |
|---|---|
| `DateTime.UtcNow` | Inject `TimeProvider` (built-in on .NET 8+), test with `FakeTimeProvider` from `Microsoft.Extensions.TimeProvider.Testing` |
| `Environment.*` | Create a minimal custom `IEnvironmentProvider` wrapping only the calls you use |

